Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class IidSet

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.HasLongSet<InstrumentId>
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.IidSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
PrintsInstruments, java.lang.Iterable<InstrumentId>
public class IidSet
extends HasLongSet<InstrumentId>
implements PrintsInstruments
A set of InstrumentIds that can be indexed by InstrumentId.

It uses the instrument-id-specific optimized maps (using GNU Trove) for better performance.

See Also:
HasLongSet, HasInstrumentIdSet, RBSet

      public <V> IidMap<V> toIidMap​(java.util.function.Function<InstrumentId,​V> valueGenerator)

    • toRBMap

      public <V> RBMap<InstrumentId,​V> toRBMap​(java.util.function.Function<InstrumentId,​V> valueGenerator)
      In some cases, we still need to convert to an old-style, non-specialized RBMap.

      Examples (Sep 2018) are cases where the code is more general and uses <K extends Investable> instead of just an InstrumentId, such as DoubleMap<K extends Investable>.

    • toIidMapWithFilteredKeys

      public <V> IidMap<V> toIidMapWithFilteredKeys​(java.util.function.Function<InstrumentId,​java.util.Optional<V>> optionalValueGenerator)
      Converts this set into an IidMap whose instrument ids are a subset of the instrument ids in this set and whose corresponding values are some function of the instrument id.

      The valueGenerator passed must return Optional.empty() if an instrument id is not supposed to go into a resulting map, and Optional.of(V) if it is.

      See Also:
      orderedToIidMap(java.util.function.Function<com.rb.biz.types.asset.InstrumentId, V>)

    • orderedToIidMap

      public <V> IidMap<V> orderedToIidMap​(java.util.function.Function<InstrumentId,​V> valueGenerator)
      This converts this set into an IidMap with the same instrument ids, and whose corresponding values are some function of the instrument id. However, the ordering that the valueGenerator is run on the instrument ids is fixed.

      This matters when valueGenerator has a side effect, such as increasing some internal counter.

      See Also:
      toIidMap(java.util.function.Function<com.rb.biz.types.asset.InstrumentId, V>)
